comments.body:
Honestly I do not understand why we use the NetNs interface on the Container State object. This requires us to open the netns to use it. If you look at the users of this interface they all call .Path() so they only want the path which means the the open is completely unnecessary and adds overhead. We should just use the path, this would also remove the need for the code
[replaceNetNS()](https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/main/libpod/boltdb_state_linux.go#L15) function which creates the error you are seeing.
@mheon WDYT?
